comments: Wyntre; no bugs encountered; instructions clear (video tutorial was well done and helpful); took me ~16 mins; notes: there's an apparent note to yourself to determine whether to include Lehigh's IRB info in the HIT intro. Also, if I recall correctly the example on the video of the potential adjustments to points showed a bump down on the left side but a bump up on the right side, which made gave me pause - if the main message was that the point range can go up or down 1, both sides showing that up/down range would've been more intuitive to me but this is probably unimportant and not worth changing.
